																		A Conclusion
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1814684&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227435" alt="GreenWolf" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1814684)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;" >GreenWolf</a></span> <span class="odate time_1509200708 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">28 Oct 2017 14:25</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3621488">
									

<p>And here it is. The third installment in this UIU series, and the final one for this plot line. Thorne and Spencer will be back for more adventures in the future.</p>
<p>Thanks to TyGently, Taffeta, Othello, Conwell, ARD, mlister, SunnyClockwork, djkaktus, and NineVolt for crit.</p>
<p>A hub will be forthcoming within the next week.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">A&nbsp;Word&nbsp;on&nbsp;Exploits&nbsp;and&nbsp;Evocations</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Is&nbsp;Sierra&nbsp;a&nbsp;Reality&nbsp;Bender?</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Just to clarify, Sierra is not a reality bender. What she is is a Type Blue (wizard) with knowledge of kinetic-related exploits. Exploits are just pattern-based reality bending, which are accessible to anyone with the knowledge and skill to implement them. They're basically the same as physics glitches in a video game that can be used to speedrun a boss or something. Exploits are usually pretty limited in scope and scale, and tend to get used a lot by anartists. Here, Sierra is using a gesture-based exploit that essentially allows her to stop projectiles heading towards her, without any of the charms or wards that Thorne is using to do the same thing.</p>
<p>Of course, since she's also a Type Blue, she can use thaumaturgy as well, which is what the freezing magic that she tries to hit Thorne with is. This is following the same thaumatology framework that Thorne's magic is using, but the backlash from her evocations isn't noticeable because she has a much greater degree of skill and control when it comes to evocations. Thorne is more of a ritual specialist, and is very much out of their element when it comes to a prolonged thaumaturgical duel.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

